<br>
If I time traveled to Wednesday and wrote down everything you did in a book, sealed the book, and then gave it to you today with explicit instructions not to open it until Thursday, does that mean that I caused everything you did on Wednesday?  No, of course not.<br>
<br>
However, I did not create the Universe.  I did not set all things into motion that would come to be, and I did not know what would come to be before I set them into motion.<br>
<br>
If at or before the very instance that God created the Universe He knew all things that would come to be, then <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  He</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is responsible for all actions, including your &quot;choices&quot;.<br>
<br>
If you are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  never</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> wrong, and built a robot, and before you even drew up the blueprints you knew the robot was going to murder 10 people, who is responsible?  You obviously are.  The robot could not have killed those 10 people if you didn't create it.  It can not avoid killing them because you are it's creator, and your posses the infallible foreknowledge of all of it's actions.  If it could have avoided killing the 10 people then you would have been wrong, and thus not infallible in your knowledge.<br>
<br>
Please explain to me in a logical manner how it could be any other way?  Please explain to me in a logical manner how the outcome seen by an infallible, omniscient creator could be avoided. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uhayzen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hayzen</A> at: 9/30/02 11:04:07 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uwolvar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolvar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>My third character is Lovawr</span><br>  Posts: 1287<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/30/02 12:55:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=43>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Free Will</span><hr size=1> Ah, so it's not the omniscience that's got you bugging, it's the creator.  Well, that's a little stickier.  It really depends on how you believed the creation was done.  Were you created specifically, were you and your forefathers all engineered down to the last decimal place?  or was a place for life created that you evolved into on your own?<br>
