<br>
You have to consider the question &quot;What is reality?&quot; though. All we have is our senses from which create perceptions of our world, and that perception is our reality. For the guy thats turning left in the car, his reality is that he can turn wherever he chooses because any fate that he has is beyond the limit of his knowlege. God (omniscient omnieverything etc.) may know better, but the guy in the car doesn't. His perception is his reality, so in his reality, there is free will. <br>
<br>
There's only one way to find out Universal Truth and that involves firearms, overdoses, fiery car crashes, and nasty stuff like that. I'll just be happy with my little perception :P<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
