<br>
I think there is a god. Whether it's the judeo-christian god or whatever I don't know and it doesn't really make a difference to me. I think in a way that it is in that I think all religions worship the same god or their roots started out that way, but that religion has become so bastardized by man steering it this way and that to conform to his own desires that we've made organized religion basically irrelevant at this point. It's a social gathering of people with common beliefs. I don't think god is omniscient in the sense that religion does, but I think he/she/it is nearly so, and for all practical purposes is omniscient to a temporal being. I also think the question of free will on a universal scale is pretty much irrelevant because I believe perception is reality. Just my 2c on the whole matter.<br>
